 Port Elizabeth - Kabega Park detectives in Port Elizabeth are searching for a suspect/s, who stabbed a 31-year-old Kuyga man to death on Thursday night. "According to police information, on Thursday at about 06:00, Lesly Magwa left his house in Kuyga to go to work," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "On Friday, at about 07:30, his body was found lying on the side of the road at the corners of Lukwe Street and Nkanyeni Drive in Kuyga. "He sustained a stab wound to his lower abdomen. "Police suspect robbery may have been the motive for the attack." A case of murder is under investigation. "Police is appealing to anyone who may have any information about the murder or the suspects/s to contact D/Sgt Ivan Klue at SAPS Kabega Park on 041 397 6867 or 0633633084." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 